              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to throw a sickle) to begin to harvest a crop by cutting ripe grain with a sickle</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to use a sickle</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to swing a sickle</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to begin to harvest</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:06601401600018} and {S:06601401900012} this idiom occurs in a figurative context, and therefore it may be necessary in some languages to speak of ‘harvesting’ rather than using a phrase which mentions the literal use of a sickle.</Comments>
